<item>
            <title>[LU-4276] make ldiskfs configured for read/write access by default</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4276</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;ext4 and hence ldiskfs in sles11 servers has config and module param options to turn on read/write access to the loaded filesystem.  Currently it is off by default.  For ldiskfs in our sles11 servers we really need it to be on by default.  It shouldn&apos;t need to be changed from default by module options in order to work correctly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I plan to push a patch to add a build time config option setting it on by default.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>sles11 sp2 and sp3 servers</environment>
        <key id="22174">LU-4276</key>
